<div class="govuk-grid-row">
  <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds-from-desktop">
    <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">Apply for the international relocation payment</h1>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="govuk-grid-row">
  <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds-from-desktop">
    <p class="govuk-body">
      The
      <%= govuk_link_to "international relocation payment (IRP)", "https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/international-relocation-payments/international-relocation-payments", { target: "_blank" } %>
      is a single payment of Â£10,000, funded by the UK government, which is
      available to eligible non-UK trainees and teachers of languages and
      physics.
    </p>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      To apply for the international relocation payment, please complete this
      form. You will need to get your documents and information ready before you
      start, as you will not be able to save your entries and return to the form
      at a later date. It should take approximately 15 minutes to complete.
    </p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Before you start, check your eligibility</h2>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      Non-uk teachers must be:
    </p>

    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>
        employed in an English secondary school
      </li>
      <li>
        teaching an eligible subject
      </li>
      <li>
        in the UK using an eligible visa
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      Non-UK trainee teachers must be:
    </p>

    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>
        training on a salaried training course leading to qualified teacher
        status and accredited by the UK government
      </li>
      <li>
        training to teach an eligible subject
      </li>
      <li>
        in the UK using an eligible visa
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      For more, visit our guidance on
      <%= govuk_link_to "the international relocation payment for teachers", "https://getintoteaching.education.gov.uk/non-uk-teachers/teach-in-england-if-you-trained-overseas#get-an-international-relocation-payment-irp-worth-10000", { target: "_blank" } %>.
    </p>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      If you are training to teach on a fee-paying training course, you do not
      have to apply to receive the international relocation payment.
      <%= govuk_link_to "The international relocation payment for trainees", "https://getintoteaching.education.gov.uk/non-uk-teachers/fees-and-funding-for-non-uk-trainees#get-an-international-relocation-payment-irp-worth-10000", { target: "_blank" } %>
      gives further information.
    </p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Documents and information to get ready</h2>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      You will need:
    </p>

    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>
        if you are a teacher, details of your employment contract, including
        teaching subject, start date and end date
      </li>
      <li>
        if you are a trainee, details of your teacher training course, including
        teaching subject and start date
      </li>
      <li>
        your visa type and when you entered the UK
      </li>
      <li>
        your passport
      </li>
      <li>
        your address in England
      </li>
      <li>
        contact details for the school where you are employed as a teacher or
        trainee
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      If you are teaching or training to teach physics or languages in
      combination with another subject, you may want to contact your employing
      school to check at least 50% of your teaching time is spent teaching
      physics or languages. For more details about this requirement, visit:
    </p>

    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
      <li>
        <%= govuk_link_to "the international relocation payment for teachers", "https://getintoteaching.education.gov.uk/non-uk-teachers/teach-in-england-if-you-trained-overseas#get-an-international-relocation-payment-irp-worth-10000", { target: "_blank" } %>
      </li>
      <li>
        <%= govuk_link_to "the international relocation payment for trainees", "https://getintoteaching.education.gov.uk/non-uk-teachers/fees-and-funding-for-non-uk-trainees#get-an-international-relocation-payment-irp-worth-10000", { target: "_blank" } %>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      <%= govuk_link_to("Start", new_applicants_application_type_path, { class: "govuk-button" })%>
    </p>

    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Contact us</h2>

    <p class="govuk-body">
      For help, please email us at
      <%= govuk_link_to("teach.inengland@education.gov.uk", "mailto:teach.inengland@education.gov.uk")%>.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
